/*
 * STAGING — active-cooling (pwm-fan) map for the A523 thermal zones. DRAFT.
 * Does NOT build against today's baseline. See dts/staging/README.md and
 * docs/THERMAL-DVFS-NOTES.md.
 *
 * BLOCKED ON: the A523 THS (thermal sensor) series is not upstream yet.
 * Latest is Mikhail Kalashnikov's "[PATCH v5] Allwinner: A523: add support for
 * A523 THS0/1 controllers" (based on 7.2-rc1; Reviewed-by Chen-Yu Tsai on 3/5
 * patches — close to merge, but not in v7.2-rc1). That series adds:
 *   - thermal-sensor@2009400 (ths1: big=idx0, little=idx1, gpu=idx2)
 *   - thermal-sensor@200a000 (ths0: dram)
 *   - thermal-zones: cpu0_thermal, cpu4_thermal, gpu-thermal, ddr-thermal
 * with passive cpufreq throttling only (each cpu has #cooling-cells = <2>).
 *
 * WHAT THIS ADDS (the missing piece): the board has a real pwm-fan
 * (label pwm_fan, 33 cooling states) that the upstream zones do NOT bind. This
 * fragment attaches the fan as an ACTIVE cooling device to the CPU zones, so
 * the device spins its fan up instead of only throttling. Include it from the
 * board DTS *after* the THS series is in the kernel tree (its zone/trip labels
 * must already exist), and add `#include <dt-bindings/thermal/thermal.h>`.
 *
 * CAVEATS (resolve on hardware):
 *  - The upstream cpu zones set `sustainable-power`, which selects the IPA
 *    (power_allocator) governor. A plain pwm-fan is not a power actor, and the
 *    upstream cpufreq cooling devices carry no `dynamic-power-coefficient`, so
 *    IPA may not modulate the fan as intended. On HW, either (a) add
 *    dynamic-power-coefficient to the CPUs + a fan cooling-map weight, or
 *    (b) drop sustainable-power to fall back to step_wise (simpler for a fan).
 *    The mapping below assumes step_wise-style ramping; tune once THS reads real
 *    temperatures on the device.
 *  - Trip points (70/90 C passive) come from the vendor BSP via the THS series;
 *    the vendor userspace thermald starts the fan far lower (auto mode). Pick the
 *    fan-start trip to taste after measuring idle/load temps.
 *  - Upstream v5 has a known bug (gpu-thermal trips node is misnamed `gpu-trips`
 *    instead of `trips`, so gpu trips are ignored) — adopt the MERGED version,
 *    not v5 verbatim. Once fixed, a gpu fan map can be added the same way.
 */

/* Ramp the fan on the little-cluster zone (also covers idle SoC temp). */
&cpu0_thermal {
	cooling-maps {
		map-fan {
			trip = <&cpu0_threshold>;	/* 70 C passive */
			cooling-device = <&pwm_fan THERMAL_NO_LIMIT THERMAL_NO_LIMIT>;
		};
	};
};

/* Ramp the fan on the big-cluster zone (the hot one under load). */
&cpu4_thermal {
	cooling-maps {
		map-fan {
			trip = <&cpu4_threshold>;	/* 70 C passive */
			cooling-device = <&pwm_fan THERMAL_NO_LIMIT THERMAL_NO_LIMIT>;
		};
	};
};
